1. Install all required packages using requirements.txt preferably in a virtual environment

2.  Use the following command to activate the virtual environment.
        source /bin/activate

3.   Install MySQL on your system using the official documentation:      
        http://dev.mysql.com/downloads/

4. Extract the database from the sqldump file using the following command:
           mysql -u root -p --one-database destdbname db.sql

5. To run the server on localhost, run the following commands:
        cd my_proj/src 
        python manage.py runserver

6. The website now is ready to use.

The screenshots of the working web application are in the 'screenshots' folder.


